At Chic Monogram, the customers are the designers! :) Since ALL of my work is custom, you DON’T have to send me a custom order request, unless you want more than 10 of any item, or have a special request that you don’t see available. STEP 2.) Once you have your design details ready, put the item(s) you want in your cart. All design details should be written to me in the “Note To ChicMonogram” portion of the order form as you are checking out. If you'd like the EXACT same design as in the photo, just give me the personalization details (note: Please write monograms in the order they should appear - First, LAST, Middle, along with the full name).

***********************************

***********************************
STEP 3.) You will receive a design proof via an Etsy message, and I will await your written approval before producing the item. We can make changes from there (up to 3 proofs) until you are happy with the design! And that’s it!!

Product name: Custom Minnie scribble shirt, Mickey sketch, family Disney shirt, disney family shirts, personalized, Mickey Mouse scribble, mickey sketch t
Description:
THis sketch Mickey is one of our all time best sellers AND we finally found MINNIE!!  
Also note that we are using the Disney Font on these instead of the sketch font.
**ORDERING**
Please include in the comments section upon checkout, specifics for EACH shirt
Shirt color-
Shirt size-
Name-
Mickey or Minnie (flower, red bow, pink bow)-
***SIZING**
Please see our sizing chart in the 4th picture - we are unfortunately NO HELP in sizing since we have a 5'8" 15yo girl and 3'1" 14 yo boy (with dwarfism).  With 5 kids with dwarfism I just no longer have there reference for "normal" sizing and went to great lengths to make sure you had the measurements you needed to make the decision on size easier.
Our mens and youth shirts run pretty true to size.
The LADIES shirt does run about 1 size small - please see measurements in the 4th picture.
Our shirts are a buttery soft fabric that will NOT shrink. 
These are our performance shirts - they are lightweight, breathable, moisture wicking and have antimicrobial features.  The white tends to be a little more see through.
We offer these in GREY and WHITE
(these white shirts are a little thin and see through so we do recommend grey)
We can ONLY get onesie's and toddler in WHITE  If you order one of these we will make and send the white.
**HOWEVER, if you need a 3T or larger there is a minimal difference (like 1/2 inch) in size between the 3T and the XS which does come in grey**
In addition, we use a vapor and heat process which adds our design directly to the fibers of the shirt.  This prevents our designs from fading AND there is no weird feeling to the shirt where our design is located.  Our sensory kids love these shirts and are NOT constantly distracted like they are with vinyl or embroidered shirts.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
We try our best to print and have your shirt out in the mail immediately (as in next day)!  PLEASE include the date you need your shirt by in the comments along with your child's name and any other special information!
PLEASE NOTE ~ computer screens differ from person to person.  We try to provide the most accurate colors in our listing but they may appear slightly different in person.  Our process DOES make for a colorful and vibrant shirt when printed on a WHITE shirt - and what we recommend for most of our t-shirts.  We know that white isn't everyone's favorite but we looked long and hard for a shirt that would stand up to kid's wear.  We do OFFER a grey t-shirt BUT it will show through the design as our process actually embed's INTO the fiber and doesn't sit on top!  Our t-shirt's are a performance tee that feels like cotton.  Although we strive for 100% satisfaction - we will not give refund's for any of the above normal variation's.

"The meaning of moonstone is closely tied to the moon. Just like the moon influences the earth and its inhabitants so does the moonstone. It has been used as a stone of protection for travelers all over the world.
It is mostly know as a stone for lovers however, it is said that if you give your lover a moonstone or a piece of moonstone jewelry that the passion you share will be eternal.
Moonstone meaning
The powers of the moonstone are deeply linked to the moon itself, focusing on love, fertility, good fortune and protection during dark times.
This ancient gemstone has been in use for thousands of years all over the world. From Ancient Rome, India and China to Middle Age Europe, it has always held an important position.
As it is a stone of love and fertility it was often used as a wedding gift or as a token of eternal love. In some traditional communities in India and the Middle-East it is still very common to present newly-weds with a moonstone.
The use as a stone of protection of travelers was also widespread, though it is hardly used for this purpose today. Which is a shame, because the reason it was used by travelers is that it would protect them not just during dark nights, but dark times in general.
With the advent of electric lighting dark nights were a thing of the past, but as we all know, dark times unfortunately are not. So if you want or need a bit of extra protection in tough times a moonstone is a good option.
To get the most out of your moonstone it should be used during an almost full or full moon. This will energize your moonstone and enhance its powers.
Moonstone is a traditional birthstone of June, alongside pearls.
Moonstone Meaning: Legends and Myths
Most of the legends and myths surrounding the moonstone focus on its connection to the moon. In particular its connection to moon goddesses like Selene, Diana and Nyx.
In many myths moonstones are either pieces of the moon itself or frozen tears that fell after a moon goddess had a lovers quarrel. Another reason why moonstones are thought to help people reconcile after they have had a fight.
Moonstone Healing Properties
Due to its connection with the moon, moonstone can help attune the body and mind to the natural forces that surround us. Helping us to get more in tune with our body."

Product name: 1940s Singer Buttonholer Attachment 121795 in Original Box
Description:
1940s Singer Buttonholer Attachment 121795 in Original Box
Aficionados of vintage Singer products are likely already familiar with Singer's patented all-in-one 'Buttonholers' from the 50s/60s with their modern plastic cases and visually appealing hardware. But before all that, buttonholing was less about marketing and more about functionality. Which is why this early-edition buttonholer from the late 1930's/early 40's somehow appears nude. Yet it performs the same duties; one still had to affix this piece to an appropriate Singer sewing machine just like any other. While this early model isn't the prettiest attachment, its advent certainly revolutionized buttonholing. 
Buttonholer comes with its original green & white box. Side of box reads, "Sold by Singer Sewing Machine Company" while the end reads, "Made in U.S.A. Singer Buttonhole Attachment No. 121795. For Singer Lock Stitch Family Sewing Machines". On the buttonholer itself is engraved "SINGER U.S.A. 121795 COMPLETE".
NOTES: Feed cover plate (and clamping screw) IS included. Original 1940s instruction booklet is NOT included, but we threw in a newer-model instruction booklet instead.
CONDITION: Box exhibits appropriate signs of age (fading, wear, etc) but otherwise intact and holding up well. There's a sticker/tape attached to the box top which we didn't try to remove. The stainless steel buttonholer hardware has no rust/pitting or oxidation (like new) and all four wingnuts are still present.

Product name: Weighted Blanket 10-15 lbs
Description:
This blanket is 40" x 60" and is available in weights from 10 lbs to 15 lbs and the following colors: Royal Blue, Silver Grey, Crimson Red, Turquoise, Aqua and Lilac. Other colors are available upon request.
We use a National Courier Broker to get the best shipping costs and Etsy's Mailing System to provide the best mailing costs for our customers. We do not charge a handling fee or add any additional charges. Please include your phone number when placing your order as we must provide it to the courier when making a shipment.
Our Windsor, Ontario company is proud of the excellent products which we offer at affordable prices. All of our products consist of FOUR LAYERS of top quality poly cotton fabric for durability and we use a UNIQUE REINFORCING STITCH on the majority of  seams for longevity. We use only VIRGIN food-grade hypo-allergenic poly pellets with smooth edges.  We never use recycled pellets.  The weight of the poly pellets is evenly distributed throughout the pockets. All of our products are machine washable using a gentle cycle and a low to medium heat setting for drying.
Poly/cotton blended products combine the softness of cotton with the durability of polyester. The combination of cotton and polyester results in a dense weave that tends to keep its shape and color. It is not prone to wrinkling, and does not shrink. The cotton component makes it more comfortable than products made solely of polyester. Blended products generally cost less and last longer than 100% cotton. That enables us to pass these savings on to our customers.
The recommended weight formula for a weighted blanket is 10% of an individual’s weight plus 1 lb. For example, a 60 lb person would use a 7 lb blanket. We are not qualified to advise anyone about the weight they should have other than the recommended weight that is standard in the industry. There are OT specialists who assess individuals with sensory disorders to determine their ideal weight. There are OT Associations throughout North America. In Canada, you could contact The Canadian Association of Occupational Therapists for assistance: www.caot.ca
Weighted blankets are therapeutically beneficial. They have helped individuals with a multitude of neurological disorders such as:
Autism Spectrum Disorder 
Sensory processing disorder (SPD)
Restless legs syndrome (RLS)
Pervasive Developmental Disorder (PDD, PDD-NOS)
Anxiety disorders
Bi-polar
Schizophrenia
Obsessive Compulsive Disorder (OCD)
Fibromyalgia
Traumatic Brain Injuries (TBI)
Attention Deficit Disorder (ADD) 
Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD)
Insomnia and other sleeping disorders
Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
Dr. Temple Grandin was diagnosed with autism in 1950. She graduated from university and to this day, she is a prominent author and world-renowned autism spokesperson. 
While she was looking into ways to treat her own anxiety, she discovered the benefits of pressure as a way to calm her overstimulated nervous system.  She created a squeeze machine for herself, which gave her relief due to the deep pressure stimulation.  Researchers and clinicians have adapted the idea into weighted blankets.  Research has found that deep pressure stimulation releases seratonin, a neurotransmitter that creates the feeling of calm and converts to melatonin, a hormone that helps regulate sleep. There are no negative effects of leaving a weighted blanket on for long periods of time.
CARE INSTRUCTIONS:
Machine wash separately in warm or cold water using a gentle cycle.
Machine dry using a low to medium heat setting.
Commercial or extra capacity machines are recommended for blankets weighing more than 15 lbs.
Do not iron. 
NEVER put weighted blankets in the microwave or oven. 
Do not dry clean. 
WARNING: Weighted blankets should never be used on infants or people who do not have the ability or strength to remove the blanket from their face or head.
Please DO NOT allow your weighted blanket to be available to your pets as chewing and clawing can cause the blanket to tear and expose the pellets.
WARRANTY:
It is not possible to have an accurate color match when the reproduction is done electronically, and/or when different dye lots are used. Therefore, we are not responsible if the actual fabric color is different from the picture(s) shown. 
We stand behind the quality and workmanship of our products. Please remember that the seller is not responsible for abuse or misuse of these items.
Our weighted products are custom made so refunds are not normally possible, unless the order is incorrect because of size, weight, fabric or color errors. 
We will replace any item which is damaged during transit, providing you ship the damaged item complete with its damaged packaging back to us within 3 days of receiving it.
Our goal is to ensure complete customer satisfaction, so please contact us if you have an issue and we will work with you to resolve your concerns.

Your contact information, shipping and billing address will only be used to communicate with you by 
me (the seller) about your order should the need arise.

Product name: 100% Natural Hard Sugar Wax - Strip-Free Face and Body Wax
Description:
This 100% Natural Strip-Free Hard Sugar Wax is made with:
Sugar
Lemon Juice
Water
Usage:
Use this wonderful, 100% Natural  Strip-Free Hard Sugar Wax to remove unwanted body or facial hair.
Directions:
1. Remove jar lid.
2. Microwave wax in 10 second intervals until the wax is pliable enough to grab a piece (do not melt the wax to a liquid state)
3. Remove a chunk of wax from the jar and begin stretching it with wet fingertips, until it is very pliable. When it is ready to use it will resemble a piece of stretchy caramel.
4. Place piece of wax across intended area and stretch in across the skin in the opposite direction of hair growth.
5. Rip wax off in the direction of the hair growth.
6. Reuse the piece of wax until entire area is free of hair, stretching wax with wet fingertips between applications. Discard wax piece when done.
2 Size Variations Available.
Packaged in a 1.0 fl. oz. Glass Jar or a 2.0 fl. oz. Glass Jar.

Product name: Custom Magic Card
Description:
Because of the featuring in vsauce's game Lut I received an enormous amount of orders. I could actually take 3 weeks to make your card, but get in line if you don't mind waiting and sooner or later it will be in your hands! I'll get to you as fast as I can, unfortunately I need to sleep from time to time!
YOU WILL RECEIVE:
1) the image I will do --------------------------------------------------------  DIGITAL
2) the MTG card you can print--------------------------------------------  DIGITAL
3) the photo you sent me and the card side by side --------------  DIGITAL
4) I'll print the card with good quality and mail it to you--------  PHYSICAL
5) An extralarge print for you to frame (glossy paper) ------------PHYSICAL
Free Shipping
❤❤❤❤❤SEE THE PRODUCT VIDEO❤❤❤❤❤
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D7rVuS4Qe5c&t=5s
❤❤❤❤❤And see all the cards I've made so far: http://www.stephanieparcus.com/cards/
HOW DOES THIS WORK? 
I'll make the card in 5-10 days and send you the digital files, so you can check and see if you like the results. If there will be anything to change, I do all the revisions for free until it's perfect. 
Color: White, Blue, Black, Red, Green, Gold
Mana Cost: How many for each color and how many colorless?
Supertype: Legendary, Basic, Snow, World, Ongoing
Type: Creature, Tribal, Artifact, Enchantment, Land, instant, Sorcery, Planeswalker, Plane, Scheme, Emblem
Subtype: Anything you want to describe what it is! ie unicorn, goblin, troll, cleric, etc
Abilities: indicate cost and full description. This can be anything you want, include abilities that exist in the game already (send link of card image for example).
Flavor: It's the sentence in Italic that says something interesting, epic, meaningful or simply funny, about the character.
Power/Toughness (attack and defense values): example 2/2, 1/4, 3/3 are medium values, but you can get crazy with 10/10 if you want!
♪♪ HOW IS THE CARD BUILT ♪♪
The front of the card is printed on a thin special paper called high resolution paper. It will be inserted together with a real card inside a transparent card sleeve. See the video linked above to verify the final results!
♪♪ ILLUSTRATION REQUIREMENTS: ♪♪
You can choose the pose and the background, send me a private message to tell me your preferences and don't forget to send some pictures!
I am currently in Italy and will create the digital files here, but for speeding up the shipping time a friend of mine will print and assemble the letter in Colorado! He prints EVERY SUNDAY and it can take from 2-8 days to arrive to your house, depending where you are in the States!
Orders to Europe will be mailed by myself, from Italy!
Take a look at my store and other custom card print listing.
Thanks :D
Steph
PS Feel free to ask me questions if you need help to figure out the perfect description!

FILL INFORMATION
Corn:
Corn is perishable. Store in a cool, dry area and away from insects and rodents. Allow bags to thoroughly dry if they get wet/damp. Corn dust is an awesome and truly genuine part of game play! It is formed as corn breaks down so over time the bags may begin to feel less full. We also offer plastic pellet fill as an alternative to the original corn fill.
All Weather:
Perfect for playing by the pool, the river, and at the beach! Also, a must have for camping trips unless you enjoy feeding the critters! Our plastic pellet fill does not break down the way corn does so your bags will have a longer life span. We go to great lengths to ensure our fill is as close to the size and weight ratio of corn as we can get it.

Product name: Worldwide – Antiquarian Tarot Guidebook
Description:
GUIDEBOOK ONLY. 
This listing is for INTERNATIONAL BUYERS of the Antiquarian Tarot Companion Guidebook only.  Please be sure to read the Shipping Note below!
If you are in the USA and want the book, please see the listing in the shop with the tarot deck for USA ORDERS. Thanks!
ABOUT THE BOOK
The Antiquarian Companion Guidebook has 396 pages with a wonderfully tactile silk laminate cover. If you are a tarot novice, it will be a great introductory primer. If you are a seasoned reader, the book offers information about the cards that you may be interested in. It includes images and details about all of the cards. You can see the Table of Contents here: http://www.divinemuses.net/divinemusings/update-antiquarian-tarot-companion-guidebook  
The initial inspiration for the Antiquarian Tarot deck was the Albano-Waite Tarot.  The principles of the Antiquarian Tarot are based on the Waite-Smith deck combined with Paul Foster Case's work, which form the foundation of the Albano-Waite deck. 
Much of the modern occult wisdom was passed down through the Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn, which scores of decks & books have drawn from. My knowledge pulls from this, as well as Hindu philosophy. Paul Foster Case also studied Hindu philosophy and that may be why I was so drawn to his work. My guidebook is largely based on the sacred tarot and occult mysticism, with some Hindu philosophy sprinkled throughout. My work leans more toward the English style of tarot and mysticism, as opposed to the French style of reading the cards.  
BOOK SIZE: 4.25" x 7" x 1" (108mm x 178mm x 25mm), 396 pages, silk laminate cover.
To see more photos of this guidebook please see the Gallery on divineMuses.net.
SHIPPING NOTE:
INTERNATIONAL ORDERS: (If your country is not listed here, please contact me for a shipping quote. Thanks.) 
ONE BOOK ONLY: Shipped via USPS First Class International Package Service. Books will be shrink-wrapped (or bubble-wrapped) and mailed in a padded envelope. Please note: if you are also ordering the tarot deck, it will be shipped separately. 
Unfortunately, I CANNOT COMBINE SHIPPING costs of the book and tarot deck. These will have two shipping costs because they are being shipped from two different locations. (The tarot deck is printed on demand and shipped by a professional playing card company.)
It is very expensive to ship this book overseas! USPS is charging 23 to the UK, EU & Australia and 16 to Canada. I had no idea how expensive it would be to ship! This is because the book is 1" (22mm) thick and weighs 13 ounces. Basically, if a padded envelope is thicker than 3/4" (19mm) USPS considers it a "package" and charges as such. I apologize for this obscene shipping cost, but it is what the United States Postal Service charges. I almost did not offer this book worldwide, but due to some interest, I'm offering it for the time being on Etsy. Please know that I am not overcharging shipping. It is just what it costs to ship this overseas. 
If you want more than one book, please contact me and I will be happy to arrange a shipping price quote for you. 
Please be aware of your import laws & how long it takes for packages to clear customs in your country. Orders shipped internationally may be subject to customs and/or VAT fees and are the responsibility of the buyer. 
Thank you!
© 2016 self-published by Maree Bento & divine Muses. All rights reserved.
